anning the Golden Age of comics to the present day, this book charts how comics have both reflected and influenced Americans’ changing attitudes towards religion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity and literaturezUnited States. 0aComic books, strips, etc.xReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aComic books, strips, etc.xSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aSuperheroesxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  amedia, pop culture, popular culture, religion, Christianity, comics, comic studies, graphic novels, dc, daredevil, hellboy, Picture Stories From the Bible, Catholic Comics, the sandman, preacher, hot stuff, ghost rider, batman, themes, tropes, iconography, marvel, archie comics, Spire Christian Comics, Seduction of the Innocent, secularism, culture wars, moral panic.40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882824740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978828247423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978828247/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles